 [-0.2222165  1.       ]]

Its noteworthy that there is medium-strong negative corelation from the -0.26862181 coefficient.

It can be concluded that as the unreliability factor increases, there is a medium-strong change that the rating of the product decreases.

This is an insightful indicator as it clarifies questions regarding unreliability.

In [30]:
# Normalization function to range 0 - 10

def normalize(values):
    mn = values.min()
    mx = values.max()
    return(10.0/(mx - mn) * (values - mx)+10)
In [31]:

# Entering a dummy product ID to get a list of 5 recommended items

# User entered value
product_id = 'B00L3YHF6O'

product_data = [data_model_norm.loc[product_id][['Count', 'Rating', 'Unreliability']].values]

recommended_products = engine.kneighbors(X=product_data, n_neighbors=5, return_distance=False)

# List of product IDs form the indexes

Recommendation System - Part II¶

Model-based collaborative filtering system

It can be used to recommend items to users based on purchase history and similarity of ratings provided by other users who bought items to that of a particular customer.

A model based collaborative filtering technique is chosen here as it helps in making predicting products for a particular user by identifying patterns based on preferences from multiple user data.

Utility Matrix based on products sold and user reviews

A utlity matrix will consist of all possible user-item preferences (ratings) details represented as a matrix. The utility matrix will be sparce as none of the users would buy all the items in the list, hence, most of the values are unknown.

Conclusion¶

The engine recommends similar products based on feature such as number of ratings, mean ratings and unreliability factor of the Product.

As seen from the above output, we can alter the number of items recommended, and using this we can integrate online sales trends into retails stores by recommending similar products to the store.

This also can be used as an added feature as a plus point when discussing item sales and profits with the stores.
